# Trivy ignore list — explicit acceptance of known low-risk CVEs in
# transitively-installed build tooling. Each entry has an expiry date
# so it gets re-evaluated rather than rotting forever.

# wheel / jaraco.context land in /app/.venv because `uv sync` uses them
# as build helpers when installing source distributions. The runtime app
# never invokes either tool (no setup.py runs, no wheel files processed
# inside the container). Real exploit path would require running
# `pip install` / `wheel install` against attacker-controlled input
# inside the production container — we don't.
# They aren't in uv.lock (build-system deps, not project deps), so the
# fix has to come from uv pulling in newer versions transitively — track
# upstream and remove this entry on next bump.
CVE-2026-24049 exp:2027-03-31
CVE-2026-23949 exp:2027-03-31
